11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Criminal Procedure
14 6–237.
15 WHEN A DEFENDANT IS CONVICTED OF OR PLEADS GUILTY TO A CRIME AND IS
16 SENTENCED TO A TERM OF IMPRISONMENT OF AT LEAST 6 MONTHS BUT NOT MORE
17 THAN 10 YEARS, THE COURT SHALL INFORM THE DEFENDANT ABOUT THE INCOME
18 TAX RECONCILIATION PROGRAM ESTABLISHED UNDER § 2–120 OF THE TAX –
19 GENERAL ARTICLE.
20 Article – Tax – General
21 2–120.
22 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
23 INDICATED.
24 (2) “JUSTICE–INVOLVED INDIVIDUAL” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS
25 CONVICTED OF OR PLEADS GUILTY TO A CRIME AND IS CURRENTLY SERVING OR,
26 WITHIN THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING 2 YEARS, HAS BEEN RELEASED AFTER
27 SERVING A TERM OF IMPRISONMENT OF AT LEAST 6 MONTHS BUT NOT MORE THAN
28 10 YEARS IN A STATE OR FEDERAL CORRECTIONAL FACILITY.
29 (3) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE INCOME TAX RECONCILIATION
30 PROGRAM.
31 (B) THERE IS AN INCOME TAX RECONCILIATION PROGRAM IN THE STATE
32 THAT IS ADMINISTERED BY THE COMPTROLLER.

SENATE BILL 295 3
1 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO ALLOW JUSTICE–INVOLVED
2 INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE UNABLE TO FILE A STATE INCOME TAX RETURN WHILE
3 INCARCERATED TO:
4 (1) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION, ESTABLISH
5 INSTALLMENT PAYMENT PLANS TO PAY ANY UNPAID INCOME TAX THAT IS DUE FOR
6 ANY TAXABLE YEAR DURING WHICH THE INDIVIDUAL IS INCARCERATED; AND
7 (2) IF APPROVED FOR AN INSTALLMENT PAYMENT PLAN, RECEIVE A
8 WAIVER FOR ANY INTEREST AND PENALTIES THAT ACCRUE ON THE UNPAID INCOME
9 TAX.
10 (D) (1) FOR ANY TAXABLE YEAR THAT BEGINS AFTER DECEMBER 31,
11 2024, BUT BEFORE JANUARY 1, 2030, A JUSTICE–INVOLVED INDIVIDUAL WHO
12 RECEIVES A NOTICE OF ASSESSMENT OF INCOME TAX DUE FOR A TAXABLE YEAR
13 DURING WHICH THE INDIVIDUAL IS INCARCERATED MAY APPLY TO THE
14 COMPTROLLER FOR AN INSTALLMENT PAYMENT PLAN.
15 (2) IF THE COMPTROLLER DETERMINES THAT THE
16 JUSTICE–INVOLVED INDIVIDUAL IS ELIGIBLE TO PARTICIPATE IN THE PROGRAM,
17 THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ESTABLISH AN INSTALLMENT PAYMENT PLAN THAT
18 ALLOWS THE INDIVIDUAL TO PAY THE UNPAID INCOME TAX OVER A PERIOD NOT
19 EXCEEDING 10 YEARS.
20 (3) IF A JUSTICE–INVOLVED INDIVIDUAL IS APPROVED FOR AN
21 INSTALLMENT PAYMENT PLAN UNDER THE PROGRAM, THE COMPTROLLER SHALL
22 WAIVE ANY INTEREST AND PENALTIES THAT ACCRUE ON THE UNPAID INCOME TAX
23 DUE.
24 (E) (1) TO CARRY OUT THE PROGRAM, THE COMPTROLLER SHALL:
25 (I) IN COLLABORATION WITH THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC
26 SAFETY AND CORRECTIONAL SERVICES, DEVELOP AN AWARENESS CAMPAIGN TO
27 INFORM THE PUBLIC AND JUSTICE–INVOLVED INDIVIDUALS ABOUT THE PROGRAM;
28 AND
29 (II) ADOPT REGULATIONS.
30 (2) THE REGULATIONS REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(II) OF THIS
31 SUBSECTION MAY INCLUDE INCOME LIMITATIONS THAT ESTABLISH ELIGIBILITY
32 FOR THE PROGRAM.

