1 (F) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1, 2026, AND EACH DECEMBER 1
2 THEREAFTER, THE COMPTROLLER SHALL REPORT TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN
3 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, ON THE
4 IMPACT OF THE PROGRAM.
5 13–604.
6 (a) The rate of interest for each month or fraction of a month is the percent equal
7 to one–twelfth of the annual interest rate that the Comptroller sets for the calendar year
8 under subsection (b) of this section.
9 (b) On or before October 1 of each year, the Comptroller shall set the annual
10 interest rate for the next calendar year on refunds and money owed to the State as the
11 percent that equals the greater of:
12 (1) (i) 13% for 2016;
13 (ii) 12% for 2017;
14 (iii) 11.5% for 2018;
15 (iv) 11% for 2019;
16 (v) 10.5% for 2020;
17 (vi) 10% for 2021;
18 (vii) 9.5% for 2022; and
19 (viii) 9% for 2023 and each year thereafter; or
20 (2) 3 percentage points above the average prime rate of interest quoted by
21 commercial banks to large businesses during the State’s previous fiscal year, based on
22 determination by the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve Bank.
23 13–606.
24 (A) For reasonable cause, a tax collector may waive interest on unpaid tax.
25 (B) THE COMPTROLLER SHALL WAIVE THE AMOUNT OF ANY INTEREST
26 ASSESSED ON UNPAID INCOME TAX DUE UNDER THIS ARTICLE IF:
27 (1) THE UNPAID INCOME TAX IS DUE FOR A TAXABLE YEAR DURING
28 WHICH THE PERSON OWING IS INCARCERATED; AND

